parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag sensor can cause the airbag to malfunction, leading to potential injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The "Service Airbag" warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the passenger airbag indicator light on the dashboard remains off or flickers
and the airbag may not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the recall repair can lead to a delay in fixing the safety issue, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The dealer is unable to obtain the necessary parts to perform the recall repair
and the vehicle owner is left without a functional airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ineffective repair of the passenger airbag sensor can lead to the continued malfunction of the airbag system, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The "Service Airbag" warning light continues to illuminate after the recall repair
and the airbag system may not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The passenger airbag indicator light is on
the passenger airbag sensor light is on
the airbag system fails to deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to turn off, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or fails to turn off
the ignition switch is difficult to turn
the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of repair parts can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The dealer informs the consumer that the parts are not available
the consumer is placed on a waiting list
the repair is delayed or cannot be completed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PPS can cause the passenger airbag to malfunction, leading to potential safety risks in the event of an accident. The faulty sensor can also cause the airbag warning light to illuminate on the dashboard, creating a distraction for the driver.
symptoms: The passenger airbag turns off or on randomly
the service airbag light appears on the dashboard
the passenger airbag is deactivated despite having a passenger over 150 pounds
the airbag warning light remains on even when there is no passenger or the passenger is not over 150 pounds.
